'''Paul Gulian Cobben''' (born 5 June 1951 in [[Amersfoort]]) is a Dutch [[philosophy|philosopher]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.refdag.nl/nieuws/binnenland/gehandicapte_kent_veel_voldoening_1_107978|title=Gehandicapte kent veel voldoening|date=February 18, 2005|work=[[Reformatorisch Dagblad]]|language=Dutch|accessdate=17 July 2011}}</ref> His main contribution to philosophy is that he has given an [[immanent critique]] of [[Georg Wilhelm Friedrich Hegel|G.W.F. Hegel's]] philosophy.
His research specializes in Hegel's [[Phenomenology of Spirit]] (1807), [[Science of Logic]] (1812) and [[Philosophy of Right]] (1821).

