{{Infobox Korean name |img= |caption= |hangul=서악서원 |hanja=西岳書院 |rr=Seoak Seowon |mr=Soak Sŏwŏn }} The '''Seoak Seowon''' is a ''[[seowon]]'' located in the neighborhood of Seoak-dong, [[Gyeongju]], [[North Gyeongsang Province]], [[South Korea]]. Seowon was a type of local [[academy]] during the [[Joseon Dynasty]] (1392–1897). It was established by local [[Confucian]] scholars especially [[Yi Jeong]] (李楨 1578 - 1607) in 1651, the second year of [[Hyojong of Joseon|King Hyojong]]'s reign, to commemorate the virtue and scholarly achievements of scholar [[Seol Chong]], and [[Choe Chi-won]] and General [[Kim Yu-sin]]. The enshrined people played important roles in the unification of [[Three Kingdoms of Korea]] into the [[Unified Silla|Silla kingdom]].<ref>(2009) [http://eguide.gj.go.kr/detail_view/Detail_view.jsp?cid=8353&tab=1 Seoak Seowon] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722140310/http://eguide.gj.go.kr/detail_view/Detail_view.jsp?cid=8353&tab=1 |date=2011-07-22 }} Gyeongju U-Tourism Organization</ref><ref>{{ko}} [http://100.nate.com/dicsearch/pentry.html?s=K&i=254158&v=42 서악서원 西岳書院] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110610060151/http://100.nate.com/dicsearch/pentry.html?s=K&i=254158&v=42 |date=2011-06-10 }} [[Nate (web portal)|Nate]] / [[EncyKorea]]</ref>
